---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '@/components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '@/components/Footer.astro';
import { site } from '@/config';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title={`Services — ${site.name}`}
  description="Custom software development and tailored tools for small businesses. We build production software by directing AI models and agents — faster, with higher quality, and more iteration than traditional approaches allow."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 pt-12 pb-20">
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold tracking-tighter mb-4">Services</h1>
    
    <p class="text-xl text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-10">
      We build production software by directing AI models and agents. The result is custom tools and applications 
      delivered faster, at higher quality, and with far more iteration than traditional development allows.
    </p>

    <!-- Custom Development -->
    <section class="mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">Custom development</h2>
      
      <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert mb-6">
        <p>
          For founders and teams who need real software built — not prototypes, but production tools that people actually use.
          We handle architecture, implementation, testing, and deployment at high speed while keeping you involved in the decisions that matter.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-3 mb-6">
        <div class="border border-[var(--border)] rounded-xl p-4">
          <div class="font-medium mb-1">What we build</div>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] space-y-1 mt-2">
            <li>• Custom web apps and internal tools</li>
            <li>• Significant features or modules for existing products</li>
            <li>• AI integrations that are actually useful (not just wrappers)</li>
            <li>• Refactors and modernization of legacy systems</li>
            <li>• End-to-end products when you don't want to build a full team yet</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-[var(--border)] rounded-xl p-4">
          <div class="font-medium mb-1">Who this is for</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-2">
            Founders who need production software shipped quickly without hiring a full engineering team.<br>
            Small teams that need custom tools or features that generic software can't provide.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
        Engagements range from focused 2–6 week projects to longer ongoing partnerships.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- SaaS for Small Businesses -->
    <section class="mb-14 border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">SaaS &amp; tools for small businesses</h2>
      
      <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert mb-6">
        <p>
          We act as a product engineering partner for small businesses that need software tailored to how they actually work — 
          not another generic tool they have to fight against.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-3 mb-6">
        <div class="border border-[var(--border)] rounded-xl p-4">
          <div class="font-medium mb-1">What we build</div>
          <ul class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] space-y-1 mt-2">
            <li>• Internal operations tools (jobs, clients, scheduling, reporting, etc.)</li>
            <li>• Client portals and self-service systems</li>
            <li>• Vertical software tailored to specific industries or business models</li>
            <li>• Coordinated small suites instead of one massive system</li>
            <li>• Custom layers on top of tools you already use</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-[var(--border)] rounded-xl p-4">
          <div class="font-medium mb-1">Why this matters now</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-2">
            What used to require either expensive agencies or years of in-house development can now be 
            delivered at a fraction of the cost and time — while still being genuinely built for how you actually work.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Why this works -->
    <section class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-10 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">Why this works</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert">
        <p>
          The real advantage isn't just speed. Because the cost of building and changing things is dramatically lower, 
          we can explore more options and iterate toward better solutions than would be practical (or affordable) 
          with traditional development.
        </p>
        <p>
          You get software that actually fits how you work — without the usual tradeoffs between speed, cost, and quality.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How we work -->
    <section class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-10 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-4">How we work</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-neutral dark:prose-invert">
        <p>
          We keep things lightweight and collaborative. You stay involved in the decisions that matter.
          We handle architecture, implementation, testing, and deployment at high speed using AI-directed workflows.
        </p>
        <p>
          Most projects start with a short conversation to understand what you're trying to achieve. 
          From there we move quickly into working software you can actually use and give feedback on.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--text-muted)] text-sm">
          Engagements typically range from focused 2–6 week projects to longer ongoing partnerships.
          See <a href="/work" class="underline hover:no-underline">example engagements →</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">Let's talk</h2>
      <p class="text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-6">
        If you're running into friction with your current tools or have something specific you need built, 
        send me a note. I'll let you know quickly whether it looks like a good fit.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
        <a
          href={`mailto:${site.author.email}?subject=Custom development project`}
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-xl bg-slate-200 px-6 py-3 text-base font-medium text-slate-900 transition hover:bg-slate-300"
        >
          Custom development project
        </a>
        <a
          href={`mailto:${site.author.email}?subject=SaaS or tools for my business`}
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-xl bg-slate-200 px-6 py-3 text-base font-medium text-slate-900 transition hover:bg-slate-300"
        >
          SaaS / tools for my business
        </a>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
        Both buttons open your email with a pre-filled subject. You can also just email me directly at 
        <a href={`mailto:${site.author.email}`} class="underline hover:no-underline">{site.author.email}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
